ZH: 不要随便得罪他人，以免引起麻烦。
EN: Don't offend others easily, so as to avoid trouble.

ZH: 他的无礼举动得罪了我。
EN: His rude behavior offended me.

ZH: 不小心的一句话可能会得罪别人。
EN: A careless remark may offend others.

ZH: 这种无礼的态度会得罪人的。
EN: This rude attitude will offend people.

ZH: 他总是得罪一些重要的人物。
EN: He always offends some important figures.

ZH: 如果你这样说话，肯定会得罪她的。
EN: If you speak like this, you will surely offend her.

ZH: 请注意你的言辞，避免得罪他人。
EN: Please watch your words and avoid offending others.

ZH: 在这个社交场合，要小心避免得罪他人。
EN: In this social occasion, be careful to avoid offending others.

ZH: 他的暴躁脾气经常感到得罪别人。
EN: His irritable temper often causes offense to others.

ZH: 如果你不改变态度，你会得罪很多人的。
EN: If you don't change your attitude, you will offend a lot of people.

ZH: 他的冷嘲热讽总是得罪别人。
EN: His sarcastic remarks often offend others.

ZH: 你对他的忽视会得罪他的。
EN: Your neglect of him will offend him.

ZH: 尽量避免得罪客户，否则我们可能会失去生意。
EN: Try to avoid offending customers, otherwise we may lose business.

ZH: 在公共场合，我们应该注意不要得罪他人。
EN: In public places, we should be careful not to offend others.

ZH: 得罪别人会给你带来不必要的麻烦。
EN: Offending others will bring you unnecessary trouble.

ZH: 每个人在言行举止上都应该避免得罪他人。
EN: Everyone should avoid offending others in their words and actions.

ZH: 不管生气到什么程度，我们都应该控制情绪，不得罪他人。
EN: No matter how angry we are, we should control our emotions and not offend others.

ZH: 对他人的宗教信仰应该保持尊重，以免得罪别人。
EN: We should respect others' religious beliefs so as not to offend them.

ZH: 礼貌待人是不得罪他人的基本原则之一。
EN: Treating people with courtesy is one of the basic principles of not offending others.

ZH: 在跟陌生人交谈时，我们要特别小心以免得罪对方。
EN: When talking to strangers, we should be extra careful not to offend them.
